I think you are probably just accessing the endpoint with the wrong path.  /actuator/ is the default path.  You can change this something else via the yaml (properties) configuration.  See management.endpoints.web.base-path.  

This is how it works for me.  Include the actuator dependency in the pom.xml.

        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-actuator&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;

Include this in your application.yml (or properties file with the &quot;.&quot; notation.)

        management:
          endpoints:
            web:
              exposure:
                include: &quot;*&quot;

Then access the metrics endpoints with

        http://yourdomain:yourport/actuator/metrics

Also read this [article][1] for more details.


  [1]: https://www.baeldung.com/spring-boot-actuators

